description:
The golden set (test/golden/golden-set.json) is lexically trivial — every query shares exact tokens with its target — so it cannot measure (a) hybrid's semantic uplift or (b) the minScore floor's precision. There is NO hybrid floor regression guard: golden-recall.test.ts runs lexOnly (never exercises minScore, engine.ts:1639); the engine.test.ts floor test uses a fake store with hardcoded rerankScores, so it pins filtering logic, not the reranker's real distribution. A qmd reranker swap (Qwen3-Reranker-0.6B -> other) would silently recalibrate DEFAULT_MIN_SCORE=0.575 with no test failing.

Tasks:
(a) add paraphrase/synonym queries (lex-hard -> force the vector/rerank path);
(b) add distractor/negative queries (must return nothing above the floor);
(c) add a hybrid floor regression test asserting on an N-run MEDIAN / tolerance band (rerankScore is non-deterministic), reusing the existing belowFloor counter (engine.ts:1989); keep it out of 'npm test' if it loads the model (mirror bench:recall).

Acceptance: harness emits a floor precision/recall curve; a CI guard trips on a reranker-distribution regression without flapping on jitter.
